> This hearty, satisfying meal is packed with classic Southern flavors—the definition of comfort food. You'll whip up crispy fried chicken bites, buttery mashed potatoes swirled with sour cream, and creamy gravy that ties each bite together. A side of crunchy, refreshing coleslaw completes the feast!

Wash and dry produce.

Peel @potatoes{12%ounce} if desired; dice into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄4 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes to #pot{} and keep covered off heat until ready to mash in Step 5.

While potatoes cook, open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Season chicken with @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @tempura batter{82%g}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a second medium bowl, toss together @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper until thoroughly combined.

> For 4 servings, use all the vinegar and 2 tsp sugar.

Set aside until ready to serve.

== Gravy ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @flour{1%tablespoon}; stir to combine. Whisk in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 1⁄2 cup plain water. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer gravy to a #small bowl{} and cover with #plastic wrap{} to keep warm. Wash and dry pan (be sure to dry pan completely before using in Step 6!).

== Mashed Potatoes ==

To pot with potatoes, add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon}; mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Keep covered until ready to serve.

== Fried Chicken Bites ==

Heat a 1⁄2-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in pan used for gravy over medium-high heat.

Transfer seasoned chicken to bowl with tempura mixture; stir to coat.

Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, add coated chicken and cook, turning occasionally, until golden brown and chicken is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, fry in batches.

Transfer chicken to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide chicken, coleslaw, and mashed potatoes between plates in separate sections. Using the back of a #spoon{}, create a well in the mashed potatoes and fill with gravy (if gravy has cooled, microwave ~{30%seconds} or until warmed through). Top mashed potatoes with scallion greens. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.